Migori GK Prison has recorded 96 positive Covid-19 cases as Kenyan prisons continue to see a spike in the infections.⁣
.⁣
Health workers have blamed the rising cases on congestion in the correctional facilities.⁣
.⁣
Nyanza Regional Prisons Commander Hassan Bugu, however, confirmed that Migori GK hast set up a quarantine block for the inmates who test positive. READ FULL ARTICLE IN THE LINK IN BIO⁣⁣⁣⁣.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣

In addition to "wearing a mask," we will continue to thoroughly implement measures such as "use a thermometer and fill a health check sheet at check-in", "complete hand washing and disinfection" and "the social distance". We appreciate your understanding and cooperation.
